{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/how-to-deploy-react-apps-to-netlify/","webpackCompilationHash":"14d5ab8bfde083b36571","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"c9fe66c9-8da3-59c4-b485-dd5e40a3db98","html":"<p>If you are a React developer, then you might have come across a situation to deploy it to a live site for testing purpose. There are various options available for deploying a React app. I love Netlify because of its simplicity and lambda functions.</p>\n<p>First, you need to create a Netlify account. Netlify offers a free plan and you can register here.. <a href=\"https://app.netlify.com/signup\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Netlify Signup</a></p>\n<p>There are two ways to deploy a React app to Netlify. One way is through Netlify CLI and another way is with Netlify website. I am going to talk only about Netlify CLI option since it’s more suited for developers.</p>\n<h5 id=\"netlify-cli\"><a href=\"#netlify-cli\" aria-label=\"netlify cli permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Netlify CLI</h5>\n<p>First, we will install Netlify CLI globally. Since we might want to use it across different projects.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> netlify-cli -g</code></pre></div>\n<p>Once we installed Netlify CLI. We need to create a production build of our React app. Use this command to create the build from the root of your project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> run build</code></pre></div>\n<p>This will create a <code class=\"language-text\">./build</code> folder which we will use it for deployment.</p>\n<p>Next, we run this command to start the deployment process.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">netlify deploy</code></pre></div>\n<p>If you are running this for the first time you might get a popup saying login to your Netlify account like this.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/cc4eb9662765463d890c863d77ac0f43/8ff1e/netlify-auth-popup.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/blog/static/cc4eb9662765463d890c863d77ac0f43/01472/netlify-auth-popup.webp 240w,\n/blog/static/cc4eb9662765463d890c863d77ac0f43/222bd/netlify-auth-popup.webp 480w,\n/blog/static/cc4eb9662765463d890c863d77ac0f43/0cbce/netlify-auth-popup.webp 800w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/blog/static/cc4eb9662765463d890c863d77ac0f43/0783d/netlify-auth-popup.png 240w,\n/blog/static/cc4eb9662765463d890c863d77ac0f43/782f4/netlify-auth-popup.png 480w,\n/blog/static/cc4eb9662765463d890c863d77ac0f43/8ff1e/netlify-auth-popup.png 800w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/blog/static/cc4eb9662765463d890c863d77ac0f43/8ff1e/netlify-auth-popup.png\"\n          alt=\"Netlify auth popup\"\n          title=\"Netlify auth popup\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Once you have authorized follow these steps to deploy.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>In the console, if it says <strong>This folder isn’t linked to a site yet. What would you like to do?</strong>. Select the option <strong>Create &#x26; configure a new site</strong>. Since we are creating a new site</li>\n<li>Next, choose a name for the site. I’ll type <code class=\"language-text\">portfolio on Netlify</code> (You can type any available name which you like).</li>\n<li>Now it will ask for the Netlify account which you want to use, So, select your account here.</li>\n<li>After that step, we will be asked to enter the deployment path. So, just type <code class=\"language-text\">./build</code> in the command prompt.</li>\n<li>Now, our site will get created and will have a draft URL which we use to test.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Now once everything is tested and looks good with draft URL. We will move on to deployment in production. Use this command.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">netlify deploy --prod</code></pre></div>\n<p>It will ask again to enter the deployment path. Just enter <code class=\"language-text\">./build</code> again.</p>\n<p>Now we will get the live URL which is where our site will be accessible.</p>\n<p>Now you might end up with <strong>Page not found error</strong> when you access the URL.</p>\n<p>This is happening because we might be using React router in our application.</p>\n<p>To fix this issue we need to create <code class=\"language-text\">_redirects</code> file inside the <code class=\"language-text\">./build</code> folder.</p>\n<p>After creating the file. Add this content to it.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">/*    /index.html  200</code></pre></div>\n<p>If you are like me and you feel this is an extra step that you have to repeat every time. Since, <code class=\"language-text\">./build</code> the folder is overwritten whenever we create a production build. It becomes painful to create the <code class=\"language-text\">_redirects</code> file now and then.</p>\n<p>So, I created this script to fix that issue.</p>\n<p>Just create the <code class=\"language-text\">netlify.js</code> file inside the root of your project.</p>\n<p><div id=\"gist97834580\" class=\"gist\">\n    <div class=\"gist-file\">\n      <div class=\"gist-data\">\n        <div class=\"js-gist-file-update-container js-task-list-container file-box\">\n  <div id=\"file-netlify-js\" class=\"file\">\n    \n\n  <div itemprop=\"text\" class=\"Box-body p-0 blob-wrapper data type-javascript \">\n      \n<table class=\"highlight tab-size js-file-line-container\" data-tab-size=\"8\">\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-L1\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"1\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-LC1\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\"><span class=\"pl-k\">const</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">fs</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">require</span>(<span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">&quot;</span>fs<span class=\"pl-pds\">&quot;</span></span>);</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-L2\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"2\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-LC2\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\">\n</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-L3\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"3\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-LC3\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\"><span class=\"pl-k\">const</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">path</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">&quot;</span>./build/_redirects<span class=\"pl-pds\">&quot;</span></span>;</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-L4\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"4\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-LC4\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\"><span class=\"pl-k\">const</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">content</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">&quot;</span>/* /index.html 200 <span class=\"pl-cce\">\\n</span><span class=\"pl-pds\">&quot;</span></span>;</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-L5\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"5\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-LC5\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\">\n</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-L6\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"6\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-LC6\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\"><span class=\"pl-smi\">fs</span>.<span class=\"pl-en\">writeFileSync</span>(path, content, {</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-L7\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"7\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-LC7\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\">  encoding<span class=\"pl-k\">:</span> <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">&quot;</span>utf-8<span class=\"pl-pds\">&quot;</span></span></td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-L8\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"8\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-netlify-js-LC8\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\">});</td>\n      </tr>\n</table>\n\n\n  </div>\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"gist-meta\">\n        <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/sukruthmk/a7ee5a2e9e9352663d1e4b46e3543a0c/raw/5f92562d3161a58ea7d962d297527eedd1e2ca31/netlify.js\" style=\"float:right\">view raw</a>\n        <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/sukruthmk/a7ee5a2e9e9352663d1e4b46e3543a0c#file-netlify-js\">netlify.js</a>\n        hosted with &#10084; by <a href=\"https://github.com\">GitHub</a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n</div></p>\n<p>After that, we might need to add this dependency to your project. So, run this command.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> i -D fs</code></pre></div>\n<p>Once this is completed. Update your <code class=\"language-text\">package.json</code> file like this.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json\"><pre class=\"language-json\"><code class=\"language-json\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">\"scripts\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"build\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react-scripts build &amp;&amp; node netlify.js\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>So, now every time you run build command it will automatically create a <code class=\"language-text\">_redirects</code> file inside the <code class=\"language-text\">./build</code> folder.</p>\n<p>You can also deploy your React app to Github. But, I will cover that in another article.</p>\n<p>Happy Hacking!</p>","fields":{"slug":"posts/how-to-deploy-react-apps-to-netlify/","tagSlugs":["/tag/web-development/","/tag/react/","/tag/netlify/","/tag/deployment/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-08-18T21:22:31.553Z","description":"Steps to build a production React app and deploy it to Netlify","tags":["Web Development","React","Netlify","Deployment"],"title":"How to deploy React apps to Netlify"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"posts/how-to-deploy-react-apps-to-netlify/"}}}